and employees are committed to safe and reliable operations for the protection of its employees, the community, and the environment.  We are proud of our 50-year operating record, during which there has never been an incident that resulted in any off-site impacts to neighboring industries, residents, the environment, or the community at large or staff.  This record has been achieved through consistent attention and total dedication by management and staff to safe operating practices and preventive maintenance.  Sea-3 has consistently made new investments in the latest technology in operating and maintaining the facility.  

All environmental, health and safety procedures and equipment cover the railcar expansion operations.  These practices form the backbone of Sea-3's dedication to our staff, the community and environment.

Sea-3 has extensive environmental, health and safety policies and procedures (P&P) as required by the EPA, FRA, OSHA, and the US-Coast Guard.  These P&Ps as well as Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) cover the safe procedures for operation and are reviewed annually and kept current.  PSM and RMP Accident Prevention Program policies include the following Table of PSM/RMP Policies & Procedures:

